@page "/"

<TyneTitle Value="Overview" />

<MudText Typo="Typo.h4">
    Introduction
</MudText>
<MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
    Tyne is a framework for creating Blazor systems running on ASP.NET Core. It is composed of three main libraries:
    <MudList Dense="true" Class="py-0">
        <MudListItem>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
                <MudLink Href="/tyne/overview">Tyne</MudLink>:
                provides core interfaces and functionality for actions, queries, results, and validation
            </MudText>
        </MudListItem>
        <MudListItem>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
                <MudLink Href="/tyne.ef/overview">Tyne.EntityFramework</MudLink>:
                provides Entity Framework integrations such as a default search implementation and paging extensions
            </MudText>
        </MudListItem>
        <MudListItem>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
                <MudLink Href="/tyne.ui/overview">Tyne.UI</MudLink>:
                provides common UI component such as forms and tables
            </MudText>
        </MudListItem>
    </MudList>
</MudText>

<MudText Typo="Typo.h5">
    Getting Started
</MudText>
<MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
    The <MudLink Href="/tyne/overview">core libraries documentation</MudLink> is a good place to start with as every other Tyne library utilises it heavily.
</MudText>
